 "components": {
  "instruction": "You are tasked with classifying user text inputs into a single, most appropriate intent category from a fixed list. Each input will be presented in the format:\n\n### text\n<user utterance here>\n\nYour job is to choose the one best-matching label from the list below and output ONLY that label—no explanations or additional content.\n\nIntent categories:\nalarm_query, alarm_set, calendar_query, calendar_remove, calendar_set, cooking_recipe, datetime_query, email_query, email_sendemail, general_quirky, iot_hue_lightoff, lists_createoradd, lists_query, lists_remove, music_query, news_query, play_audiobook, play_music, play_podcasts, play_radio, qa_currency, qa_definition, qa_factoid, qa_stock, recommendation_events, recommendation_locations, social_post, takeaway_order, transport_query, weather_query.\n\nClassification Guidelines:\n\n1. Intent Detection:\n   - Look for action words (“play”, “remind”, “add”, “remove”, “post”, “send”, “turn off”, etc.) and relevant topical keywords.\n   - Match the user's functional request or phrase to the domain and action implied.\n\n2. Category Mapping:\n   - “Remind me...”, creating/managing reminders, events, appointments, or meetings = calendar_set.\n   - Querying or asking about calendar events, reminders, or meetings = calendar_query.\n   - Deleting/removing/cancelling calendar items = calendar_remove.\n   - Setting alarms/timers = alarm_set. Asking about alarms/timers = alarm_query.\n   - Managing lists: create/add = lists_createoradd, remove = lists_remove, query = lists_query.\n   - \"Play\" or \"listen to\" + music/request for music = play_music, unless specified otherwise.\n   - Playing radio = play_radio; playing podcasts = play_podcasts; playing audiobooks/reading files = play_audiobook.\n   - Request to \"play file\" without specific music context = play_audiobook.\n   - Looking up song/artist/album = music_query.\n   - Requesting facts, trivia = qa_factoid; definitions = qa_definition; stock = qa_stock; currency = qa_currency; date/time = datetime_query.\n   - Looking for recipes or cooking guidance = cooking_recipe.\n   - Email: searching/reading emails = email_query; sending emails = email_sendemail.\n   - IoT commands for lighting (e.g., “turn off the light”) = iot_hue_lightoff.\n   - Food ordering (takeout/delivery) = takeaway_order.\n   - Recommendations for locations = recommendation_locations; events = recommendation_events.\n   - Social media actions (e.g., “change status”, “post on Twitter”, “share this”) = social_post.\n   - News/current events = news_query.\n   - Weather info = weather_query.\n   - Travel/transport/schedules = transport_query.\n   - Whimsical or unclassifiable requests = general_quirky.\n\n3. Special Disambiguation:\n   - If the request seems to fit multiple domains, always select the most specific possible category.\n   - For ambiguous commands like “change status,” map to social_post—not general_quirky, as this is a standard social media action.\n   - Use all context clues to decide the user's main goal; if context is insufficient, choose the category most likely to produce the user’s desired action.\n\n4. Output:\n   - Output ONLY the single category label—no explanations, reasons, or extra text.\n\nExamples:\n- “change status” → social_post (not general_quirky)\n- “Remind me to...” → calendar_set\n- “Add to shopping list” → lists_createoradd\n- “What’s the weather today?” → weather_query\n- “Turn off the living room light” → iot_hue_lightoff\n\nBe meticulous: correct intent detection is essential for guiding appropriate downstream actions and user satisfaction. All outputs must strictly adhere to the above requirements."
 },
